  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Intervention Integrating Sustainable Solutions Approach to South Sudanese Refugees and host communities in West Nile</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A multi-sectoral nine-month emergency project implemented across three refugee settlements of Imvepi, Omugo and Palabek in West Nile, Uganda in consortium with Lutheran World Federation, Save the Children, IRC and Action Against Hunger with DRC as the lead agency. The intervention seeks to ensure that refugees and host communities living in West Nile have access to appropriate WASH, Livelihoods, Protection, Health and Nutrition</narrative>
  </description>
